         <p>What might seem to work well when using conrefs in English content might not work well
            when the content is translated. Here are a few guidelines that you will understand after
            completing this lesson: </p>
         <ul class="- topic/ul ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Donâ€™t use conref with ph to replace parts of a sentence.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Use extreme caution when using conref to reuse whole sentences.
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">When you do conref, do it with whole block elements that meet
                  the following requirements: <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The reused content is grammatically independent.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The referenced element and referencing element are
                           within the same context.</p>
                     </li>
                  </ul>
               </p>
            </li>
         </ul>
